89.description:
Sigma IT Poland is a division within NEXER GROUP – a custom software development company. In Poland, we started in 2017 and now we are 150+ crew with an office in Wrocław, Warsaw, and any day Cracow. We have the opportunity to work with world-renowned brands from Scandinavia, the UK, and Western Europe. Our goal is to grow strong, rather in competencies than in pure numbers.
If you like what we do, see our offer, maybe it is you we will have the pleasure to meet! :)

We are looking for a Team Manager.In the role of Team Manager, you will lead a consultancy unit focused on digital solutions for the automotive industry. You will be responsible for people &amp; delivery management. You will report to Business Unit Manager and work closely with CEO and COO as well as clients. On the daily basis, you will deal with the recruitment, development, and performance management of your team. You will be also engaged in boosting and maintaining relationships with customers. Acting as an account manager you will reply to customer requests in collaboration with sales and business development teams. You will be accountable for the unit's financial performance and for achieving company-wide goals. Your competencies will help to support our company in defining the business development line.You might be the perfect match if you have:

Experience in managing software delivery teams;
Excellent interpersonal and communication skills;
People management experience as Team Manager, Project Manager, or in a similar role;
Fluent in English (at least B2 level).

Moreover, we appreciate skills in these areas: 

 Software engineering background;
 Experience in managing teams and projects utilizing backend, front-end, and CI/CD solutions.
 By joining us, you gain the following: 
Interesting projects that you will play a crucial role in a multi-national environment; (Actually, we work with companies from industries such as music, logistics, telecommunications, social services, entertainment, Smart-Home, automotive, and bioinformatics.)
Fully remote work for your convenience or in our office in Wrocław or Warsaw;
Choice of employment form: we offer B2B or employment contract;

Flexible working hours with no micro-management approach. Our core hours are 9-15, the rest of the working time is your decision;
We provide high-quality work equipment + additional monitor and accessories;

We respect your private life so you don't have to work overtime or on weekends;

Personal Training Budged and Passion Day - an extra day off for your passion, hobby, and growth to spend as you please;

Online and offline integration events - including remote X-mass party and annual WOW tour trip abroad - so far we've been in Cape Town and Barcelona;
Free benefits such as Luxmed, Multisport, and life insurance in Nationale Nederlanden.



If you apply for this position and match our expectations, then:
1) You will be invited for an interview with Katarzyna Podejko – Business Unit Manager and Agnieszka Dombrowska –Recruitment Manager;2) You will have a final meeting with Maciej Reutt – our CEO, and Katarzyna Czupryńska-Garbat – Chief People Officer.Submit your application online in one easy step! Apply now!
